<p><strong></strong><span>Welcome to <strong><a href="https://www.meetup.com/bostonphp/events/292137096/">Agile Appetizer, Season 7</a></strong>.</span><span> Let's begin.</span></p>
<p><span>This is the first and only sprint. It will last two weeks. Once you complete this sprint you will receive a Badge to post to your LinkedIn profile. To demonstrate your commitment to begin this virtual self-study group opportunity, post a message to </span><strong><a href="https://www.meetup.com/bostonphp/messages/boards/thread/54151272">Introduce Yourself</a></strong><span> to your fellow Boston PHP members. We have seven life-long learners who have signed up to begin this agile journey.</span></p>
<p>Next, gain access to <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/learning/paths/career-essentials-in-generative-ai-by-microsoft-and-linkedin">­</a>the <strong><a href="https://kickoff.pmi.org/">Project Management Institute (PMI) Kickoff</a></strong> program. This introductory course is FREE. There are two project management courses<span>—</span><strong>Agile</strong> and Predictive (Waterfall). This virtual self-study group will focus on the <strong>Agile</strong> course. Feel free to complete the Predictive course on your own. Each course will take you approximately one hour to complete. Once you complete the <strong>Agile</strong> course, post a message, along with a link to your badge, in the <strong><a href="https://www.meetup.com/bostonphp/messages/boards/thread/54151272">Introduce Yourself</a> </strong>discussion area. This will help us gauge progress among participants.</p>
<p>Welcome aboard. Let's get agile!</p>
